-- Germany’s Woehrl May Seek Thomas Cook’s Condor Airline, SZ Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-04-15T18:18:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/germany-s-woehrl-may-seek-thomas-cook-s-condor-airline-sz-says.html
German investor Rudolf Woehrl is
interested in bidding for  Thomas Cook Group Plc (TCG) ’s Condor
airline, Sueddeutsche Zeitung reported in a preview of an
article to be published tomorrow, citing an interview.  Thomas Cook  wants more than 300 million euros ($393
million) for the unit, Sueddeutsche cited Woehrl as saying.  Woehrl bid 220 million euros with a group of investors to
acquire 52 percent of  Air Berlin Plc (AB1)  shares a few months ago,
before the carrier agreed a deal with  Etihad Airways , the
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt at 
